    "causal_summary": "The mcp-coco-index fork supported multiple embedders and exposed 023C retrieval fingerprints, but compatibility remained warning-only. Existing indexes could be queried with a different model, vector dimension, query prompt, document prompt, or corpus root. In a multi-project daemon, one loaded embedder could also be reused across project contexts even when the runtime fingerprint changed.",
